### Define Library Proxy Factory for Next.js Middleware

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/backend-for-frontend.mdx

Shows how a library can provide a `proxy` factory to create middleware, typically named `createMiddleware`. This pattern allows for encapsulating proxying logic that can be applied to requests, potentially abstracting away complex routing or transformation logic. It's noted that `proxy` might still be referred to as `middleware` by libraries.

```ts
import { createMiddleware } from 'third-party-library'

export default createMiddleware()
```

