### Define Next.js Middleware Output Structure (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/05-config/01-next-config-js/adapterPath.mdx

This TypeScript type specifies the structure for a Next.js middleware function, if present in the application. It includes the middleware's ID, file path, a fixed pathname ('/_middleware'), source page, runtime environment, assets, and a configuration object that can contain `maxDuration`, `preferredRegion`, `env`, and an array of `matchers` for defining request routing conditions.

```typescript
{
  type: 'MIDDLEWARE'
  id: string
  filePath: string
  pathname: string      // Always '/_middleware'
  sourcePage: string    // Always 'middleware'
  runtime: 'nodejs' | 'edge'
  assets: Record<string, string>
  wasmAssets?: Record<string, string>
  config: {
    maxDuration?: number
    preferredRegion?: string | string[]
    env?: Record<string, string>
    matchers?: Array<{
      source: string
      sourceRegex: string
      has: RouteHas[] | undefined
      missing: RouteHas[] | undefined
    }>
  }
}
```

